\(I_1(x)\): intensive of electron on detector screen when only slit 1 is open.

\(I_{12}(x)\): intensive of electron on detector screen when both slits are open.

\(h_1(x)\): “height” or “amplitude” when only slit 1 is open.

\(h_2(x)\):

\(h_{12}(x)\):

\[ I_1 = h_1^2 \\ I_2 = h_2^2 \\ I_{12} = h_{12}^2 = (h_1 + h_2)^2 \neq I_1 + I_2 \]

Add detector to see whether an electron goes through slit 1 or 2.
